quran[70]{c,v,t}:
  26,111,"They said, \"should we believe you, and the most decrepit closely follow you"
  26,112,"He said, \"What knowledge have I of whatever they were doing"
  26,113,"Decidedly their reckoning (falls) upon no one except my Lord, if you are aware"
  26,114,And in no way would I drive away the believers
  26,115,Decidedly I am nothing except an evident warner
  26,116,"They said, \"Indeed, decidedly in case you do not refrain, O Nuh, (Noah) indeed you will definitely be one of the stoned"
  26,117,"He said, \"Lord! Surely my people have cried me lies"
  26,118,"So arbitrate between me and them a (conclusive) arbitration, and deliver me safely and the ones who are with me of the believers"
  26,119,"So We delivered him, and the ones with him, in the laden ship"
  26,120,Thereafter We drowned afterwords the remaining ones
  26,121,Surely in that is indeed a sign; and in no way were most of them believers
  26,122,"And surely your Lord, He is indeed The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Merciful"
  26,123,Aad cried lies to the Emissaries
  26,124,"As their brother H?d said to them, \"Will you not be pious"
  26,125,Surely I am for you a trustworthy Messenger
  26,126,"So be pious to Allah, and obey me"
  26,127,And in no way do I ask of you any reward for (this); decidedly my reward (falls) upon no one except The Lord of the worlds
  26,128,"Do you build on every prominence a sign, sporting? (i.e., huge prominence inspiring fear)"
  26,129,"And do you take to yourselves castles (Or: huge buildings and tombs) that possibly you may abide eternally"
  26,130,"And when you assault, you assault as potentates"
  26,131,"So be pious to Allah, and obey me"
  26,132,And be pious to Him Who has supplied you with whatever you know
  26,133,"He has supplied you with cattle (Ancam includes cattle, camels, sheep, and goats) and sons"
  26,134,And gardens and springs
  26,135,Surely I fear for you the torment of a tremendous Day
  26,136,"They said, \"It is equal to us, whether you admonish or you are not one of the admonishers"
  26,137,Decidedly this is nothing except the character of the earliest (people)
  26,138,And in no way will we be tormented
  26,139,"So they cried him lies, then We caused them to perish. Surely in that is indeed a sign; and in no way were most of them believers"
  26,140,"And surely your Lord, He is indeed The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Merciful"
  26,141,Thamud cried lies to the Emissaries
  26,142,"As their brother Salih said to them, \"Will you not be pious"
  26,143,Surely I am for you a trustworthy Messenger
  26,144,"So be pious to Allah, and obey me"
  26,145,And in no way do I ask of you any reward for (this); decidedly my reward (falls) upon no one except The Lord of the worlds
  26,146,Will you be left secure in what you have here now
  26,147,In gardens and springs
  26,148,"And plantations, and palm trees with spathes slender (and) digestible? (Or: heavy spthes)"
  26,149,And you (skillfully) hew houses out of the mountains
  26,150,"So be pious to Allah, and obey me"
  26,151,And do not obey the command of the extravagant
  26,152,"Who corrupt in the earth, and do not act righteously"
  26,153,"They said, \"Surely you are only one of the utterly bewitched"
  26,154,"In no way are you (anything) except a mortal, like us. Then come up with a sign, in case you are one of the sincere"
  26,155,"He said, \"This is a she-camel. To her is a (time of) drinking and to you (another time of) drinking, on a known day"
  26,156,And do not touch her with an odious (treatment) so that there takes you (away) the torment of a Tremendous Day
  26,157,"Yet they hamstrung her, (and) so they became remorseful"
  26,158,"Then the torment took them (away). Surely in that is indeed a sign, and in no way were most of them believers"
  26,159,"And surely your Lord, He is indeed The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Merciful"
  26,160,The people of Lut (Lot) cried lies to the Emissaries
  26,161,"As their brother L?t said to them, \"Will you not be pious"
  26,162,Surely I am for you a trustworthy Messenger
  26,163,"So be pious to Allah, and obey me"
  26,164,And in no way do I ask of you any reward for (this); decidedly my reward (falls) upon no one except The Lord of the worlds
  26,165,Do you come up to (stout) males of the worlds
  26,166,"And leave behind what your Lord created for you as spouses? No indeed, (but) you are an aggressive people"
  26,167,"They said, \"Indeed in case you do not refrain, O L?t, indeed you will definitely be of the driven out"
  26,168,"He said, \"Surely I am of the disfavorers of your doing. (i.e., idisapprove of what you are doing)"
  26,169,Lord! Deliver me safely and my family from whatever they do
  26,170,So We delivered him safely and his family all together
  26,171,Except an old woman among the laggards
  26,172,Thereafter We destroyed the others
  26,173,"And We rained on them a rain, so odious is the rain of them that are warned"
  26,174,"Surely in that is indeed a sign, and in no way were most of them believers"
  26,175,"And surely your Lord, He is indeed The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Merciful"
  26,176,"The companions (i.e., inhabitants) of the Thicket cried lies to the Emissaries"
  26,177,"As Shuaayb said to them, \"Will you not be pious"
  26,178,Surely I am for you a trustworthy Messenger
  26,179,"So be pious to Allah, and obey me"
  26,180,And in no way do I ask of you any reward for (this); decidedly my reward (falls) upon no one except The Lord of the worlds